{"type":"message","id":"a8a28c29","parentId":"d3531a97","timestamp":"2026-03-24T00:20:47.028Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_9c6acd0an24p_2","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-23 201036\r\n\r\n## Applied Mutations\r\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\r\nRejected: research/TIC-SIGNIFICANCE-SCORING.md (missing)\r\n\r\n## LLM Response\r\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the most impactful next action.\r\n\r\nFrom the context:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 (architecture analysis) are complete\r\n2. The key insight is COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY - causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n3. Next action is the TIC Experiment (Temporal Invariance Compression)\r\n4. Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n5. Need to implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next step is to start implementing the TIC classifier. Let me look at what files exist:\r\n- `logs/pulse_*.md` - the pulse logs\r\n- Need to implement the classifier\r\n\r\nI'll create the TIC classifier script. This should:\r\n1. Load recent pulse logs (last 20 as specified)\r\n2. Identify invariants (things that persist across pulses) vs variants (things that change)\r\n3. Use invariants to predict next pulse content\r\n\r\nLet me create a PowerShell script for this since that's the environment (pulse.ps1).\r\n\r\nThe script should:\r\n1. Read the last N pulse logs\r\n2. Extract features that are invariant vs variant\r\n3. Classify content\r\n4. Measure prediction accuracy\r\n\r\nLet me write this implementation.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC Experiment is the critical next step to validate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis. I need to implement a classifier that identifies invariant vs variant content across pulse logs and tests prediction accuracy.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `src/tic-classifier.ps1` - the Temporal Invariance Compression implementation that will analyze pulse logs to identify invariants, classify content, and measure prediction accuracy against success criteria.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # TIC Classifier - Temporal Invariance Compression\r\n# Tests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n# Success: >70% classification accuracy, >60% prediction accuracy\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$NumPulses = 20,\r\n    [string]$LogDir = \"logs\"\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n\r\n# ---- Data Structures ----\r\nclass PulseData {\r\n    [string]$Filename\r\n    [datetime]$Timestamp\r\n    [hashtable]$Features\r\n    [System.Collections.ArrayList]$Invariants\r\n    [System.Collections.ArrayList]$Variants\r\n    [double]$Significance\r\n}\r\n\r\n# ---- Feature Extraction ----\r\nfunction Extract-Features {\r\n    param([string]$Content)\r\n    \r\n    $features = @{}\r\n    \r\n    # Extract goals mentioned\r\n    $goalMatches = [regex]::Matches($Content, '## (Active|Completed|Pending|Phase \\d+)')\r\n    $features.Goals = ($goalMatches | ForEach-Object { $_.Value }).Count\r\n    \r\n    # Extract file references\r\n    $fileMatches = [regex]::Matches($Content, '`(research|src|logs|state)[^`]*`')\r\n    $features.Files = ($fileMatches | ForEach-Object { $_.Value }).Count\r\n    \r\n    # Extract insights (numbered or bold)\r\n    $insightMatches = [regex]::Matches($Content, '\\*\\*(.+?)\\*\\*|\\d+\\. (.+)')\r\n    $features.Insights = $insightMatches.Count\r\n    \r\n    # Extract action items\r\n    $actionMatches = [regex]::Matches($Content, '- \\[ \\]|- \\[x\\]|\\[ACTION\\]|\\[ \\]')\r\n    $features.Actions = $actionMatches.Count\r\n    \r\n    # Extract key metrics/numbers\r\n    $metricMatches = [regex]::Matches($Content, '\\d+%|>\\d+%|\\d+/\\d+')\r\n    $features.Metrics = $metricMatches.Count\r\n    \r\n    # Extract architecture names\r\n    $archMatches = [regex]::Matches($Content, 'TemporalAttention|Compositional|Infant|Breakaway')\r\n    $features.Architectures = ($archMatches | Select-Object -ExpandProperty Value | Sort-Object -Unique).Count\r\n    \r\n    # Code/script presence\r\n    $features.HasCode = ($Content -match '```|function |param\\(') ? 1 : 0\r\n    \r\n    # Key phrases (indicators of causal relationships)\r\n    $causalPhrases = @('because','therefore','causes','results in','if-then','implies',\r\n                       'due to','as a result','mechanism','enables','allows','drives')\r\n    $features.CausalIndicators = ($causalPhrases | Where-Object { $Content -match $_ }).Count\r\n    \r\n    return $features\r\n}\r\n\r\n# ---- Invariant Detection ----\r\nfunction Find-Invariants {\r\n    param(\r\n        [PulseData[]]$Pulses,\r\n        [double]$Threshold = 0.7\r\n    )\r\n    \r\n    $allFeatures = @{}\r\n    \r\n    # Collect all features across all pulses\r\n    foreach ($pulse in $Pulses) {\r\n        foreach ($key in $pulse.Features.Keys) {\r\n            if (-not $allFeatures.ContainsKey($key)) {\r\n                $allFeatures[$key] = @()\r\n            }\r\n            $allFeatures[$key] += $pulse.Features[$key]\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    $invariants = @()\r\n    $variants = @()\r\n    \r\n    # Calculate variance for each feature\r\n    foreach ($featureName in $allFeatures.Keys) {\r\n        $values = $allFeatures[$featureName]\r\n        $mean = ($values | Measure-Object -Average).Average\r\n        $stdDev = [Math]::Sqrt(($values | ForEach-Object { [Math]::Pow($_ - $mean, 2) } | Measure-Object -Average).Average)\r\n        \r\n        $cv = ($stdDev -eq 0) ? 0 : ($stdDev / [Math]::Max([Math]::Abs($mean), 0.01\r\n\r\n## For Next Instantiation\r\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\r\n- Completed at: 2026-03-23 20:11:01"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1005,"aggregated":"# Pulse: 2026-03-23 201036\r\n\r\n## Applied Mutations\r\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\r\nRejected: research/TIC-SIGNIFICANCE-SCORING.md (missing)\r\n\r\n## LLM Response\r\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the most impactful next action.\r\n\r\nFrom the context:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 (architecture analysis) are complete\r\n2. The key insight is COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY - causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n3. Next action is the TIC Experiment (Temporal Invariance Compression)\r\n4. Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n5. Need to implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next step is to start implementing the TIC classifier. Let me look at what files exist:\r\n- `logs/pulse_*.md` - the pulse logs\r\n- Need to implement the classifier\r\n\r\nI'll create the TIC classifier script. This should:\r\n1. Load recent pulse logs (last 20 as specified)\r\n2. Identify invariants (things that persist across pulses) vs variants (things that change)\r\n3. Use invariants to predict next pulse content\r\n\r\nLet me create a PowerShell script for this since that's the environment (pulse.ps1).\r\n\r\nThe script should:\r\n1. Read the last N pulse logs\r\n2. Extract features that are invariant vs variant\r\n3. Classify content\r\n4. Measure prediction accuracy\r\n\r\nLet me write this implementation.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC Experiment is the critical next step to validate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis. I need to implement a classifier that identifies invariant vs variant content across pulse logs and tests prediction accuracy.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `src/tic-classifier.ps1` - the Temporal Invariance Compression implementation that will analyze pulse logs to identify invariants, classify content, and measure prediction accuracy against success criteria.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # TIC Classifier - Temporal Invariance Compression\r\n# Tests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n# Success: >70% classification accuracy, >60% prediction accuracy\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$NumPulses = 20,\r\n    [string]$LogDir = \"logs\"\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n\r\n# ---- Data Structures ----\r\nclass PulseData {\r\n    [string]$Filename\r\n    [datetime]$Timestamp\r\n    [hashtable]$Features\r\n    [System.Collections.ArrayList]$Invariants\r\n    [System.Collections.ArrayList]$Variants\r\n    [double]$Significance\r\n}\r\n\r\n# ---- Feature Extraction ----\r\nfunction Extract-Features {\r\n    param([string]$Content)\r\n    \r\n    $features = @{}\r\n    \r\n    # Extract goals mentioned\r\n    $goalMatches = [regex]::Matches($Content, '## (Active|Completed|Pending|Phase \\d+)')\r\n    $features.Goals = ($goalMatches | ForEach-Object { $_.Value }).Count\r\n    \r\n    # Extract file references\r\n    $fileMatches = [regex]::Matches($Content, '`(research|src|logs|state)[^`]*`')\r\n    $features.Files = ($fileMatches | ForEach-Object { $_.Value }).Count\r\n    \r\n    # Extract insights (numbered or bold)\r\n    $insightMatches = [regex]::Matches($Content, '\\*\\*(.+?)\\*\\*|\\d+\\. (.+)')\r\n    $features.Insights = $insightMatches.Count\r\n    \r\n    # Extract action items\r\n    $actionMatches = [regex]::Matches($Content, '- \\[ \\]|- \\[x\\]|\\[ACTION\\]|\\[ \\]')\r\n    $features.Actions = $actionMatches.Count\r\n    \r\n    # Extract key metrics/numbers\r\n    $metricMatches = [regex]::Matches($Content, '\\d+%|>\\d+%|\\d+/\\d+')\r\n    $features.Metrics = $metricMatches.Count\r\n    \r\n    # Extract architecture names\r\n    $archMatches = [regex]::Matches($Content, 'TemporalAttention|Compositional|Infant|Breakaway')\r\n    $features.Architectures = ($archMatches | Select-Object -ExpandProperty Value | Sort-Object -Unique).Count\r\n    \r\n    # Code/script presence\r\n    $features.HasCode = ($Content -match '```|function |param\\(') ? 1 : 0\r\n    \r\n    # Key phrases (indicators of causal relationships)\r\n    $causalPhrases = @('because','therefore','causes','results in','if-then','implies',\r\n                       'due to','as a result','mechanism','enables','allows','drives')\r\n    $features.CausalIndicators = ($causalPhrases | Where-Object { $Content -match $_ }).Count\r\n    \r\n    return $features\r\n}\r\n\r\n# ---- Invariant Detection ----\r\nfunction Find-Invariants {\r\n    param(\r\n        [PulseData[]]$Pulses,\r\n        [double]$Threshold = 0.7\r\n    )\r\n    \r\n    $allFeatures = @{}\r\n    \r\n    # Collect all features across all pulses\r\n    foreach ($pulse in $Pulses) {\r\n        foreach ($key in $pulse.Features.Keys) {\r\n            if (-not $allFeatures.ContainsKey($key)) {\r\n                $allFeatures[$key] = @()\r\n            }\r\n            $allFeatures[$key] += $pulse.Features[$key]\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    $invariants = @()\r\n    $variants = @()\r\n    \r\n    # Calculate variance for each feature\r\n    foreach ($featureName in $allFeatures.Keys) {\r\n        $values = $allFeatures[$featureName]\r\n        $mean = ($values | Measure-Object -Average).Average\r\n        $stdDev = [Math]::Sqrt(($values | ForEach-Object { [Math]::Pow($_ - $mean, 2) } | Measure-Object -Average).Average)\r\n        \r\n        $cv = ($stdDev -eq 0) ? 0 : ($stdDev / [Math]::Max([Math]::Abs($mean), 0.01\r\n\r\n## For Next Instantiation\r\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\r\n- Completed at: 2026-03-23 20:11:01","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774311647026}}
